{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 13:34:33.232686", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content=\"Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nTopology and context\\n- Hosts: host_1 (10.0.0.1/24), host_2 (10.0.0.2/24)\\n- Switches: switch_1 (connected to host_1 on eth0/port1 and to switch_2 on eth1/port2), switch_2 (connected to host_2 on eth0/port1 and to switch_1 on eth1/port2)\\n- P4 program: bloom_filter.p4 with IPv4 LPM table MyIngress.ipv4_lpm; bloom filter logic only applied when TCP is parsed\\n\\nSummary of observed behavior\\n- End-to-end reachability is broken: pings time out in both directions.\\n  - host_1 -> host_2: ping timed out\\n  - host_2 -> host_1: ping timed out\\n- Host interfaces are up and correctly addressed; static ARP entries exist for peer IP/MAC.\\n  - host_1 eth0: 10.0.0.1/24, RX 0, TX 6\\n  - host_2 eth0: 10.0.0.2/24, RX 0, TX 6\\n  - ip neigh on host_1: 10.0.0.2 lladdr 00:00:0a:00:00:02 PERMANENT\\n  - ip neigh on host_2: 10.0.0.1 lladdr 00:00:0a:00:00:01 PERMANENT\\n- Inter-switch link is operational:\\n  - switch_2 logs show forwarding of packets out port 2 (toward switch_1).\\n  - switch_1 logs show packets being received on port 2 (from switch_2).\\n\\nKey findings from switch logs\\n- switch_2 (healthy forwarding state):\\n  - For traffic to 10.0.0.1, MyIngress.ipv4_lpm returns a hit and forwards to port 2 with correct MAC rewrite; TTL is decremented and checksum updated.\\n  - Example log: Table 'MyIngress.ipv4_lpm': hit with handle 1 for 0a000001/32; Action MyIngress.ipv4_forward ... egress_spec=2; Transmitting out port 2.\\n\\n- switch_1 (faulty forwarding state):\\n  - For traffic to 10.0.0.2, MyIngress.ipv4_lpm returns a miss and executes MyIngress.drop (default drop).\\n  - Example log: Applying table 'MyIngress.ipv4_lpm' with key 0a000002; Table 'MyIngress.ipv4_lpm': miss; Action MyIngress.drop; Dropping packet.\\n  - Critically, switch_1 log shows a control-plane action clearing the LPM table before the drops:\\n    - At startup, the LPM table was populated:\\n      - 10.0.0.1/32 -> port 1\\n      - 10.0.0.2/32 -> port 2\\n    - Then at 13:29:04.227: bm_mt_clear_entries on MyIngress.ipv4_lpm\\n    - Default entry subsequently set to MyIngress.drop\\n  - After the clear, all LPM lookups on switch_1 become misses and are dropped, both for packets arriving from host_1 (port 1) and from switch_2 (port 2).\\n\\nAssessment of bloom filter logic\\n- The bloom filter actions only apply when hdr.tcp.isValid() is true.\\n- ICMP ping packets (protocol 1) do not trigger TCP extraction; logs confirm hdr.tcp.isValid() is false.\\n- Therefore, bloom filter logic is not the cause of the current drops.\\n\\nAnomaly detection\\n- Abnormal condition: Loss of all IPv4 LPM entries on switch_1 with default action set to drop.\\n- Symptom: Complete loss of L3 forwarding at switch_1, leading to 100% packet loss and zero RX on both hosts.\\n\\nLocalization of fault\\n- Fault localized to switch_1:\\n  - switch_2 forwards correctly (LPM hits).\\n  - Inter-switch link works (packets observed arriving at switch_1 port 2).\\n  - Hosts are configured correctly and can transmit (TX counters increment), but receive nothing (RX 0) due to drops at switch_1.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- Control-plane action cleared the IPv4 LPM table on switch_1 (bm_mt_clear_entries at 13:29:04.227) and left the default action as drop. With no LPM entries, switch_1 drops traffic destined to both 10.0.0.1 and 10.0.0.2, breaking bidirectional reachability.\\n\\nAdditional notes\\n- Attempt to dump tables via bmv2_table_dump returned a tool-side syntax error, but bmv2 runtime logs provide definitive evidence of table state and behavior.\\n- ARP is not a factor due to permanent neighbor entries on both hosts.\\n- The observed packet parsing and deparsing confirm ICMP is correctly recognized and normal forwarding would occur if LPM entries were present.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- Network health: Degraded (end-to-end traffic dropped).\\n- Faulty device: switch_1 (MyIngress.ipv4_lpm table state).\\n- Root cause: Control-plane cleared LPM entries on switch_1 and enforced default drop, causing all IPv4 forwarding to fail at that switch., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.\" additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='85aa91e9-3b1b-4826-bd54-5a1b501586b3'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
